article.description: Tanner Leissner scored 20 points to lead seven in double figures and New Hampshire rolled over Division III Worcester State 100-66.
article.headline: New Hampshire rolls over Worcester State 100-66
article.linkText: New Hampshire rolls over Worcester State 100-66
article.story: DURHAM, N.H. -- Tanner Leissner scored 20 points to lead seven in double figures and New Hampshire rolled over Division III Worcester State 100-66. Leissner was 9 of 17 from the field and grabbed 12 rebounds. Iba Camara scored a career-high 18 points with 15 rebounds. Joe Bramati was among four with 11 points apiece, and added seven assists and three steals. New Hampshire (6-3) shot over 53 percent and hit 6 of 16 beyond the arc. The Wildcats outrebounded their smaller opponents 52-34. Worcester State was led by Alex Santos with 18 points and Paul Brooks added 10 points and nine boards. New Hampshire never trailed. It was tied at eight a little over four minutes in when the Wildcats went on a 24-point run -- holding Worcester State scoreless over an 8:22 stretch. New Hampshire led 46-23 at the half. Pat McNamara, Jacoby Armstrong and Daniel Dion all contributed 11 points and Ronnel Jordan had 10.
